      title: 'XYZprinting Extends Its Professional Additive Manufacturing Leadership With New Products and Rapidly Expanding Reseller Network',
      author_name: 'XYZprinting',
      online_date: 'Nov 13, 2018 12:00:00 AM',
      offline_date: 'Dec 31, 5000 12:00:00 AM',
      category: 1,
      region: 2,
      saved_date: 'Aug 16, 2019 2:58:10 PM',
      content: '<ul>\r\n\t<li>&nbsp;<span style="font-size:20px"><strong>Introducing Several New Professional-Grade 3D Printers</strong></span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:20px"><strong>Announcing the Addition of New European Resellers</strong></span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:20px"><strong>Leveraging the Manufacturing Power of NKG to Deliver Affordably </strong></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px">Frankfurt, Germany, November 13, 2018 &ndash; XYZprinting, the world leading 3D printer brand, today announced that as part of its commitment to extends its professional 3D printing category leadership it plans to unveil three new products at FormNext 2018. In connection of this announcing, the company plans to further extent its global reseller network with introducing few new European reselling partners.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px">&ldquo;We are excited about the significant progress we made since our foray into the professional segment exactly one year ago right here at FormNext both in terms of new and affordable printers based on our own development and the rapid expansion of our global reseller channel.&rdquo;, said Simon Shen, Chief Executive Officer, New Kinpo Group, one of the largest global electronics contract manufacturing and parent of XYZprinting.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px">&ldquo;At NKG, we have been pioneering and practicing industry 4.0 by deploying our own 3D printing solutions into our entire product design and manufacturing process throughout our factories worldwide. We are thrilled to show case some of those case stories here this year.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px">&ldquo;We remain strongly committed to innovation and democratization of access to professional 3D printer and are dedicated to productizing affordable mission critical products.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px">&ldquo;The breadth of our key portfolio products spanning affordable professional-grade Laser Sintering, Binder Jetting, Continuous Printing and Filament Extrusion printers, has caught the attention of leading category reseller around the world who prize delivering higher performance and lower cost of ownership to their customers&rdquo; said Michele Marchesan, Senior Vice President, Industry 4.0.&rdquo;.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px">&ldquo;In line with that; we are very pleased to announce that Logicom of France, New Office Automation3D AM of Italy, Promech of Middle East region, Seeda 3D Printing Systems &amp; Solutions of Netherlands and more global resellers have joined our rapidly expanding channel with more resellers joining us here at FormNext as we continue to build the best and most professional access for our customers the world over.&rdquo;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px"><strong>The company has started and expects to expand its early access program for its new products throughout 2018 and commence commercial shipments of its professional 3D printers early in 201</strong><strong>9 </strong><strong>delivering the full benefit of its expanded product performance.. With the imminent arrival of its new systems, the company invites interested customers to apply for its early access program and</strong>&nbsp;<strong>qualified resellers and end-users alike to visit </strong><strong>its booth </strong><strong>at <strong>FormNext Hall 3.1 stand D10, November 13rd &ndash; 16th and find out how you can join our early access program. </strong></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:12px"><strong><em>About XYZprinting:</em></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:12px"><em>XYZprinting is a leading global provider of comprehensive 3D printing solutions. XYZprinting is the number one global brand in desktop 3D printing products and services and is now moving decisively into the industrial additive manufacturing arena.</em></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:12px"><em>XYZprinting is backed by the world&rsquo;s leading electronic manufacturing conglomerate, New Kinpo Group, which earns more than 36 billion dollars revenues annually and has more than 8,500 engineers in research and development across four continents. With nearly two decades of design and manufacturing experience, New Kinpo Group is a recognized manufacturer of many of today&rsquo;s printers for both personal and commercial use.</em></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:12px"><em>Read more about us at </em><a href="http://pro.xyzprinting.com/"><em>http://</em><em>pro.xyzprinting.com</em></a></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:12px"><strong><em>About New Kinpo Group:</em></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:12px"><em>New Kinpo Group is a leading global electronic manufacturing services (EMS) and original design manufacturing (ODM) company that offers customers lower costs, faster delivery and world-class product quality. The New Kinpo Group includes well-known subsidiaries such as Cal-Comp, XYZprinting, Kinpo Electronics and AcBel. The company&rsquo;s EMS business spans multiple product lines, including storage, printers, network-attached storage (NAS), wireless and broadband, digital home, consumer electronics, wearables, 3D printing, robotics, power management and smart grid, industrial, automotive, security, medical/healthcare and emerging technologies. </em></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:12px"><em>XYZprinting is a wholly-owned subsidiary of NKG and a leading global provider of comprehensive 3D printing solutions. XYZprinting is the number one selling global brand in desktop 3D printing products and services since 2015 and is now moving decisively into the industrial additive manufacturing arena.</em></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:12px"><strong>For more information, visit&nbsp;</strong><a href="http://en.newkinpogroup.com/"><strong>http://en.newkinpogroup.com/</strong></a></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:12px"><strong>MEDIA CONTACT </strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:12px">Marketing and PR Communications</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:12px">Gary Shu</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:12px">E-mail: <a href="mailto:garyshu@xyzprinting.com">garyshu@xyzprinting.com</a>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n',
